The u64 type is defined in `types.h`:

    #ifdef BIGENDIAN
    typedef struct {
    	u32 h;
    	u32 l;
    } u64;
    #else
    typedef struct {
    	u32 l;
    	u32 h;
    } u64;
    #endif

So it appears that the `.l` and `.h` members represent the &quot;low&quot; and &quot;high&quot; 32 bits of a 64-bit number.

